<subSubSection lastPageId="59" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,1465,2029]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1681,1706]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pronotum orange, elytra dull reddish brown; head between eyes yellow; posterolateral corners of V7 rounded, not appearing produced in dried pinned specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,1465,2029]" lastBlockId="59.[151,1436,151,1543]" lastPageId="59" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,266,1753,1777]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Male.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[277,428,1753,1777]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.15" metricValueMax="6.8" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="6.15" valueMax="6.8" valueMin="5.5">5.5––6.8 mm</quantity>
long. Colour (
<figureCitation box="[603,738,1753,1777]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 83–86</figureCitation>
): pronotum dull deep orange; retraction of fat body beneath cuticle leaving irregularly shaped darker areas; pronotal punctures margined in deeper orange; MS and MN yellow; elytra deep reddish brown, dusky brown on humeral angle, basal 1/4 of epipleuron and basal 1/8 of sutural ridge narrowly dusky orange; (pubescence of dorsal body appears golden yellow under high illumination; if not so illuminated elytral surface appears dull); head between eyes pale clear yellow, semitransparent (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1333,1897,1921]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
); labrum light brown; apices of palpi dark brown; scape and pedicel dark red brown, shiny, FS dull dark brown; pro and mesosterna and pleura yellow; coxae, trochanters 1, 2 and femora 1, 2 yellow; tibiae, tarsi and apices of femora 1, 2 dark brown; ventral surface of metathorax medium brown; coxae 3 brown; anterior face trochanters 3 brown, posterior face yellow; femora 3 yellow except for brown apical fourth; remainder of legs 3 brown; basal abdominal ventrites dark brown; V5 dark brown, with irregular white markings across posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1222,1307,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 87</figureCitation>
); V6 and 7 white; basal abdominal tergites dark brown; terminal 3 tergites very pale brown, semitransparent, T8 narrowly brown along lateral and posterior margins (
<figureCitation box="[630,759,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Figs 88, 90</figureCitation>
); dorsally uprolled lateral margins of V6 and 7 creamy white (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 88</figureCitation>
). Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[403,492,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
): 
<quantity box="[516,606,295,319]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
wide, 
<quantity box="[691,781,295,319]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
long; W/L = 1.3; midanterior margin broadly rounded, projecting considerably beyond angulate anterolateral corners; lateral margins subparallel; punctures contiguous over most of disc. Elytra (
<figureCitation box="[449,534,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
): dull, with dense subcontiguous punctures. Head: GHW 
<quantity box="[1190,1329,367,391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.4 mm</quantity>
; SIW 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
; ASD &lt;ASW. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[493,618,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Figs87, 88</figureCitation>
): posterior margin of V7 not trisinuate, posterolateral corners appearing rounded and not produced posteriorly in pinned specimens, and slightly angulate in ethanol preserved specimens; LOs occupying most of V7, reaching sides but not posterior margin; MPP medianly shallowly emarginated or truncate, L=W. T8 (
<figureCitation box="[378,464,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 90</figureCitation>
): Ventral surface with well developed lateral ridges and short, wide rounded flanges. Aedeagus: prolongation of ML short and wide; lateral margins of LL straight, not expanded along outer ½; apices obliquely truncate; L/W=6.0. Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation box="[684,767,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 89</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" startId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" targetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" targetPageId="58">
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1437,1910,2024]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,343,1910,1933]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">FIGURES 83–91.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2013" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[353,649,1910,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pharusaurea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[353,649,1910,1932]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Australoluciola pharusaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[659,743,1911,1932]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[659,743,1911,1932]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,151,1543]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,620,644]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Female.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[300,385,620,644]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
long; coloured as for male except for narrowly white posterior margin of V5; white LO in V6 only; V7 pale in median area (due to fat body), dark laterally and along posterior margin; V8 brown. Bursa plates (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,692,716]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–91" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1910,1933]" captionTargetBox="[177,1421,193,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-83@58.[177,1421,193,1886]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 83–91. Australoluciola pharusaurea sp. nov. (83–89 holotype male ANIC; 90 paratype male G648 ANIC; 91 paratype Kerevat female ANIC). 83 dorsal; 84 pronotum dorsal; 85 anterior head; 86 left lateral apical palpomeres maxilla and labium, apical labial palpomere arrowed; 87, 88 abdomen ventral (87) and dorsal; 89 aedeagal sheath dorsal; 90 Tergite 7, 8 ventral; 91 bursa lateral. Figure legends: 2 posterior plate, 3 anterior plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265378/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,151,1543]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,728,752]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[583,725,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pharusaurea">
<emphasis box="[583,725,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">pharusaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[pharus (Greek) = lighthouse and aureus (Latin) = golden] emphasizes the pattern of light production observed for 
<specimenCount box="[774,875,764,788]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
which &quot;emitted 40 consecutive flashes without an omission&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Lloyd, J. E." box="[278,432,799,823]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="991 - 1008" refId="ref127038" refString="Lloyd, J. E. (1973 a) Fireflies of Melanesia: Bioluminescence, Mating Behavior, and Synchronous flashing. Environmental Entomology, 2 (no. 6), 991 - 1008." type="journal article" year="1973">Lloyd, 1973a</bibRefCitation>
), as well as the golden colour of the head and pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,151,1543]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,836,860]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="McDermott, F. A." box="[325,540,836,860]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="98 - 118" refId="ref127730" refString="McDermott, F. A. (1966) Lampyridae Pars. 9. Coleopterorum Catalogus (Junk-Schenkling) (Ed. Sec), 1 - 149 (Luciolini, 98 - 118)." type="book chapter" year="1966">McDermott (1966)</bibRefCitation>
recorded only 
<taxonomicName authority="Olivier" authorityName="Olivier" box="[719,989,836,860]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leucura">
<emphasis box="[719,901,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Luciola leucura</emphasis>
Olivier
</taxonomicName>
from New Britain, but listed six New 
<collectingCountry box="[151,232,871,895]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Guinea</collectingCountry>
species having orange pronotum, and uniformly dark elytra. All were described with a trisinuate posterior margin to V7, inconsistent with this species. Of these 
<taxonomicName box="[758,936,908,932]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venusta">
<emphasis box="[758,936,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Luciola venusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[991,1093,908,932]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="timida">
<emphasis box="[991,1093,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">L. timida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may not be from New 
<collectingCountry box="[1355,1436,908,932]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and are discussed; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="1966" box="[364,536,944,968]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveicollis">
<emphasis box="[364,536,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Aus. foveicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Olivier. Ballantyne &amp; McLean" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[592,709,944,968]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupilla">
<emphasis box="[592,709,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">M. pupilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterised here. 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E." box="[978,1140,943,967]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="333 - 374" refId="ref128538" refString="Olivier, E. (1885) Catalogue des Lampyrides faisant partie des collections du Musee Civique de Genes. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, (2 a) 2, 333 - 374." type="journal article" year="1885">Olivier (1885)</bibRefCitation>
based 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier. McDermott" authorityYear="1966" box="[1220,1436,944,968]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anthracina">
<emphasis box="[1220,1436,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Luciola anthracina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on a female; male specimens assigned subsequently (
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E." box="[774,943,980,1004]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="417 - 422" refId="ref129050" refString="Olivier, E. (1913 b) Lampyridae. Resultats de L'Expedition Scientifique Neerlandaise a la Nouvelle-Guinee en 1907 et 1909 sous les auspices de Dr H. R. Lorentz. Zoologie Livraison III. Nova Guinea, 9, 417 - 422." type="journal article" year="1913">Olivier, 1913b</bibRefCitation>
) were described with trilobed V7 and the ventral surface of the abdomen black except for the white V6 and 7 and white posterior margin of V5 (males are redescribed here). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[362,562,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pharusaurea">
<emphasis box="[362,562,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Aus. pharusaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier. McDermott" authorityYear="1966" box="[715,896,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anthracina">
<emphasis box="[715,896,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Aus. anthracina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its distribution, ventral colouration, and non trisinuate posterior margin of V7. 
<taxonomicName box="[549,746,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficollis">
<emphasis box="[549,746,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Luciola ruficollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described with black head, V7 trilobed, ventral thorax reddish and ventral abdomen yellow [
<bibRefCitation author="Guerin-Meneville, F. E." box="[574,866,1124,1148]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refId="ref125132" refString="Guerin-Meneville, F. E. (1838) Insectes. In: Lesson, M. (Ed.) Voyage autour du monde, execute par ordre du roi, sur la corvette de sa majeste, La Coquille, pendant les annees 1822, 1823, 1824, et 1825 etc. Zool. 2, Pt. 2, Div. 1, Ch. xiii. Bertrand: Paris, pp. 57 - 302." type="journal volume" year="1838">Guérin-Méneville (1838)</bibRefCitation>
]. 
<bibRefCitation author="McDermott, F. A." box="[884,1113,1124,1148]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="98 - 118" refId="ref127730" refString="McDermott, F. A. (1966) Lampyridae Pars. 9. Coleopterorum Catalogus (Junk-Schenkling) (Ed. Sec), 1 - 149 (Luciolini, 98 - 118)." type="book chapter" year="1966">McDermott's (1966)</bibRefCitation>
reference to Plate XXXV in 
<bibRefCitation author="Girard, M." box="[151,307,1159,1183]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" refId="ref124888" refString="Girard, M. (1873) Les Insectes. Traite elementaire d'entomologie. Introduction. Coleopteres. Tome 3. Paris." type="book" year="1873">Girard (1873)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName box="[358,490,1160,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficollis">
<emphasis box="[358,490,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">L. ruficollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is to a species with lateral prolongations of the antennal FS, inconsistent with any known 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu McDermott" authorityYear="1966" box="[235,358,1196,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciolinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Luciolinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[369,584,1196,1220]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="117 - 170" refId="ref122195" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 a) Further Revisional Studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113, 117 - 170." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne (1987a)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName box="[720,948,1197,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennata">
<emphasis box="[720,948,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Pteroptyx antennata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1003,1134,1196,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficollis">
<emphasis box="[1003,1134,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">L. ruficollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be conspecific. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pharusaurea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Aus. pharusaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[442,573,1232,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficollis">
<emphasis box="[442,573,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">L. ruficollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its darker ventral colouration and presently known distribution. The latter is not identifiable in collections, and is treated under 
<emphasis box="[745,937,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Species Incertae.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,151,1543]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<bibRefCitation author="Lloyd, J. E." box="[199,360,1303,1327]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="991 - 1008" refId="ref127038" refString="Lloyd, J. E. (1973 a) Fireflies of Melanesia: Bioluminescence, Mating Behavior, and Synchronous flashing. Environmental Entomology, 2 (no. 6), 991 - 1008." type="journal article" year="1973">Lloyd (1973a)</bibRefCitation>
observed that no more than 
<specimenCount box="[679,793,1303,1327]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
of this species were seen flying at any one time, and that these &quot;emitted series of single short flashes ... with a period of about 0.5 seconds&quot;, and he described the pursuit of a flying female by a male. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[450,652,1376,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pharusaurea">
<emphasis box="[450,652,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Aus. pharusaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sympatric in 
<collectingRegion box="[846,988,1375,1399]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="West New Britain" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">New Britain</collectingRegion>
with the orange head 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<taxonomicName class="Acidimicrobiia" family="Med" genus="Medeopteroptyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Acidimicrobiales" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Actinobacteriota" rank="species" species="effulgens">Medeopteroptyx effulgens</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
males of which flashed &quot;single short flashes at a flash period of about 1.2 secs&quot;, contrasting with a flash period of 0.5 secs for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[400,599,1448,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Australoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pharusaurea">
<emphasis box="[400,599,1448,1472]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Aus. pharusaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These two orange headed species from 
<collectingRegion box="[1062,1201,1447,1471]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="West New Britain" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">New Britain</collectingRegion>
are morphologically distinctive, differing in colour, punctation of pronotum and elytra, pronotal outline, and possession of the deflexed elytral apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
